<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>Use Skeleton if you wish to manually create the joints of a skeleton for use with skinned meshes. This is mainly of use to people creating editors, tooling, or dynamic skeletons. It is more common that a Qt 3D application would simply consume an existing skeleton and skinned mesh as created in a digital content creation tool such as Blender. For this use case, please see <db:link xlink:href="qml-qt3d-core-skeletonloader.xml">SkeletonLoader</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:section>
